Package: howdy-secure
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: p3ngwen <jeremy@goodguytek.com>
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Depends: tpm2-tools, python3, python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, gir1.2-vte-2.91,
 gir1.2-ayatanaappindicator3-0.1, libpam-python, libpam0g
Recommends: howdy
Description: Seamless GNOME Keyring unlock via face auth and TPM2
 After a successful Howdy face-authentication login, Howdy Secure
 automatically unlocks your GNOME Keyring — no password popup.
 .
 Your keyring password is sealed into the TPM at setup time and can
 only be unsealed on the same machine. A recovery code is generated
 for TPM-reset or kernel-update scenarios.
 .
 Includes a GTK3 installer wizard (howdy-secure-installer) and a
 system tray management app (howdy-secure-app) for ongoing use.
 .
 Note: Howdy itself requires the ppa:boltgolt/howdy PPA. The included
 installer wizard handles this automatically.
